    <note>Tang(2) Yantong(zi) [21527] Tang Geng, WJ, 16.3a-4b (wife, born Shi(5), who died in 1088 at age 56). (On page 4b of funerary inscription, Geng [1598] specifically refers to himself as a son of born Shi(2)'s husband). Tang Geng, WJ, 16.1a-3a is the funerary inscription for Geng's father, and again refers to himself as son. See also 16.5a-5b. The discrepancy between this inscription and that for Geng's brother Dan [21528] in which Dan is identified as the eldest of three sons, whereas Yantong(zi) has five sons, can be explained by the common copying error where a wu becomes as san. CBD, 3, 1788.名未詳，彥通其字。</note>
